  • Constructor Details

    • Appointment

      public Appointment​(int appointmentId, java.lang.String title, java.lang.String description, java.lang.String location, java.lang.String type, java.lang.String start, java.lang.String end, java.lang.String createDate, java.lang.String createdBy, java.lang.String lastUpdate, java.lang.String lastUpdatedBy, int customerId, int userId, int contactId) throws java.lang.Exception
      Constructor for creating a valid appointment.
      Parameters:
      appointmentId - An integer pulled from the Appointment_ID field from the database
      title - A string pulled from the Title field from the database.
      description - A string pulled from the Description from the database.
      location - A string pulled from the Location field from the database.
      type - A string pulled from the Type field from the database.
      start - A string representing a date/time pulled from the Start field from the database.
      end - A string representing a date/time pulled from the End field from the database.
      createDate - A string representing a date/time pulled from the Create_Date field from the database.
      createdBy - A string representing a user pulled from the Created_By field from the database.
      lastUpdate - A string representing a date/time pulled from the Last_Update field from the database.
      lastUpdatedBy - A string representing a user pulled from the Last_Updated_By field from the database.
      customerId - An integer pulled from the Customer_ID field from the database.
      userId - An integer pulled from the User_ID field from the database.
      contactId - An integer pulled from the Contact_ID field from the database.
      Throws:
      java.lang.Exception - Throws Exception if there is a problem in the Fetcher class.
